{"tid":2439773,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"［快閃英語］學好英文冇你諗到咁難","createTime":"2021-03-09T13:03:05.000Z","updateTime":"2021-03-24T12:36:00.000Z","uid":127052,"like":44,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":24,"replies":[{"pid":"ce948e5979d796de4c694ba89e65fa9f463b08b9","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:03:05.000Z","msg":"利申 英文廢<br />\n我見好多人學英文忽略咗最重要嘅一環<br />\n就係Collocation<br />\nCollocation係指 用字配搭<br />\n<br />\n例如<br />\n「我睇緊電視」「我睇緊書」<br />\n英文會話 I am watching TV / I am reading a book<br />\n中文嘅 睇 係萬能Key 「睇緊女 睇緊電視 睇緊書 睇緊路」<br />\n英文嘅 動詞 就要注意配搭<br />\n電視 要用 watch<br />\n書 要用 read<br />\n<br />\n又例如<br />\nHappy 呢個字 係 「開心」<br />\n但除咗 I am happy, I am very happy, I am not happy之外<br />\n你識唔識其他用法？<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ozdic.com/collocation-dictionary/happy\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ozdic.com%2Fcollocation-dictionary%2Fhappy&d=eGp%2FCvHI00KNC8mlo1Mhy8RCHeky4xD%2FQbA%2BfbsvJuc%3D&h=403ec79a\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ozdic.com/collocation-dictionary/happy</a><br />\n以下列舉 形容詞 開心 「Happy」嘅常見配搭字<br />\nhappy adj.<br />\n<br />\nVERBS<br />\nappear, be, feel, look, seem, sound<br />\nOutwardly the couple appeared happy. Andrew felt happier than he had been for a long time.<br />\n| become | make sb<br />\nMoney won't make you happy.<br />\n| keep sb<br />\nHe went home from time to time, to keep his mother happy.<br />\n<br />\nADV.<br />\nextremely, only too, particularly, really, very<br />\nWe'd be only too happy to accept your invitation.<br />\n| completely, perfectly, quite<br />\nMum seemed perfectly happy with my explanation.<br />\n| genuinely, truly<br />\nFor the first time in her life, she felt truly happy.<br />\n| far from, not altogether, not at all, not entirely, not exactly, not particularly, not too, not totally<br />\nHer boss was not entirely happy about the situation.<br />\n| fairly, pretty, reasonably, relatively | just<br />\nI'm just happy to be back home.<br />\n| absurdly, amazingly, blissfully, deliriously, ecstatically, radiantly, ridiculously, strangely, surprisingly | clearly, obviously<br />\n<br />\nPREP.<br />\nabout<br />\nI'm not too happy about her attitude.<br />\n| for<br />\nSo you're getting married, I hear. I'm really happy for you!<br />\n| with<br />\nI was quite happy with the way things went.<br />\n<br />\n如果你學一個字 但唔學佢嘅配搭詞 唔學佢其他用法<br />\n純粹係 I am, he is, she is, they are<br />\n咁你只係 認得 個字<br />\n你冇學識點樣用呢個字"},{"pid":"62482e41c013ce0b5eb1e1cfdc89e080e6c556c2","tid":2439773,"uid":12623,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:03:32.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/read.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2880679ab79cd7031f170e7eeba72150b05ef78a","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":11,"dislike":3,"score":8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:07:29.000Z","msg":"講多一個 常見好多人用錯嘅字<br />\nCost 大約譯做 「值」<br />\nQ: How much does this cost?<br />\nA: It costs $10<br />\n聽落冇問題<br />\n<br />\n咁如果問返之前呢？<br />\nQ: How much did this cost?<br />\n<strong>A: It costed $10</strong><br />\n咁就唔啱了<br />\n<br />\nCost呢個字 指 「值」嘅時候<br />\nPast Tense 過去式 都係 Cost 唔係Costed<br />\nCosted係指 「估價」<br />\ne.g. I costed this job = 我對呢件工作做咗估價<br />\n<br />\n所以係<br />\nQ: How much did this cost?<br />\nA: It cost $10<br />\n咁就啱啦<br />\n<br />\n所以唔好見到 有Past Tense喎 過去式喎<br />\n加ED 就實啱啦<br />\n要知道一個動詞都可以有幾個意思"},{"pid":"6ec7e8abb5635d824847b8b2a691664f556189b1","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:12:55.000Z","msg":"覺得好難 睇新聞 好多生字唔識"},{"pid":"628e54b7cea58e48975808f662ffb7a48e4d2f2a","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:13:25.000Z","msg":"講多一個Collocation<br />\nPromise ＝ 承諾<br />\n如果當名詞用<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ozdic.com/collocation-dictionary/promise\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ozdic.com%2Fcollocation-dictionary%2Fpromise&d=eGp%2FCvHI00KNC8mlo1Mhy8RCHeky4xD%2FQbA%2BfbsvJuc%3D&h=861d7340\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ozdic.com/collocation-dictionary/promise</a><br />\npromise noun<br />\n<br />\n1statement that you will do sth<br />\nADJ.<br />\nbig<br />\nHe makes all kinds of big promises he has little intention of keeping.<br />\n| rash | broken, unfulfilled | empty, false, hollow | vague | binding, firm | campaign, election, pre-election<br />\n<br />\nVERB + PROMISE<br />\ngive sb, make (sb)<br />\nYou gave me your promise I could use the car tonight. I'll consider it, but I make no promises.<br />\n| fulfil, honour, keep | break, go back on | extract<br />\nWe extracted a promise from them that they would repay the money by May.<br />\n| hold sb to<br />\nThe Opposition is determined to hold the government to its election promises.<br />\n<br />\nPREP.<br />\n~ about<br />\nThey've made all sorts of promises about reforming the health system.<br />\n| ~ of<br />\npromises of support<br />\n<br />\n你可以話<br />\nHe fulfilled his promise, he kept his promise, he honoured his promise = 佢遵守承諾<br />\nHe broke his promise, he went back on his promise<br />\n佢反口<br />\n<br />\n咁你話 喂 我好耐啦喎 點樣再進步？<br />\n咁就要學啲 比較唔常見 但照樣有人用嘅 配搭<br />\nWe extracted a promise from them that they would repay the money by May.<br />\n你話 Extract 唔係 「抽走」「拎走」咁解咩？<br />\n啱 咁樣係一個用法<br />\n但你查字典睇睇<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/nPNqJ0n.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FnPNqJ0n.png&h=e2d95df1&s={SIZE}\" /> <br />\nExtract可以指 <br />\nobtain (something such as money or information) from someone unwilling to give it.<br />\n&quot;I won't let you go without trying to extract a promise from you&quot;<br />\n<br />\n咁你同時 又學到Collocation 「Extract可以跟Promise用」<br />\n又學到 Extract 呢個字嘅新用法<br />\n<br />\n你用呢個方法學英文 先係學緊<br />\n唔係記生字咁簡單 <img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f4a13f7ede3f30d8f492d9ca805f19de5b8c0015","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"6ec7e8abb5635d824847b8b2a691664f556189b1","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:12:55.000Z","msg":"覺得好難 睇新聞 好多生字唔識"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:14:06.000Z","msg":"你追呢個Po追貼啲<br />\n我諗到嘢會放上嚟講"},{"pid":"4c1046f1addd59cc3f71ba560860187fed3b433e","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"f4a13f7ede3f30d8f492d9ca805f19de5b8c0015","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"6ec7e8abb5635d824847b8b2a691664f556189b1","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:12:55.000Z","msg":"覺得好難 睇新聞 好多生字唔識"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:14:06.000Z","msg":"你追呢個Po追貼啲<br />\n我諗到嘢會放上嚟講"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:15:26.000Z","msg":"發音 拼音都係 SAD<br />\nBTW thanks 巴打"},{"pid":"2cd93cba03e841f5d6679a71b06848858f9840de","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"4c1046f1addd59cc3f71ba560860187fed3b433e","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"f4a13f7ede3f30d8f492d9ca805f19de5b8c0015","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"6ec7e8abb5635d824847b8b2a691664f556189b1","tid":2439773,"uid":268956,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:12:55.000Z","msg":"覺得好難 睇新聞 好多生字唔識"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:14:06.000Z","msg":"你追呢個Po追貼啲<br />\n我諗到嘢會放上嚟講"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:15:26.000Z","msg":"發音 拼音都係 SAD<br />\nBTW thanks 巴打"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-09T13:18:22.000Z","msg":"英文發音係有啲難度<br />\n但英文比起 例如話法文發音 少咗強制連音<br />\n如果係好輕嘅連音<br />\nNothing at all (at-all) 其實聽多一兩次都聽得出<br />\n聽 相當應該冇咁難<br />\n<br />\n同埋英文文法比較合理 少啲變化"},{"pid":"0da32c36fcd030e66e83c04ea00fc4aabec225e6","tid":2439773,"uid":286206,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f4a13f7ede3f30d8f492d9ca805f19de5b8c0015","tid":2439773,"uid":127052,"